22:00 AFTERPARTY

Erasmus Festival

17th of September, Brno

Going on an adventure to a new country while not knowing anybody around? Maybe it's a surprise, maybe not, but you're not alone! Believe me or not, everybody feels a bit scared about making new connections. Can at least something make it easier?

Yeah, a festival! Just imagine: music playing in the background; you just finished a burger and took a sip of beer, the sun is shining, and you're looking around. Chill with others in the corner with the water pipes? Have a drink, cotton candy? Talk to people you enjoyed the flag parade with or dance with the crowd in front of the main stage. Maybe DJ on the second stage will make your day. It's upon you!

On the 17th of September, all international students from Brno will be in the crowd walking through the city centre of Brno. They will be dancing, singing and holding the flags of their home countries. Then they'll be dancing to the music in the Festival area and enjoying the Festival atmosphere.

Will you be there as well?
Buy your ticket in one
of the ESN offices.
